00:44:51.810 --> 00:44:58.890
to talk about, to tell us about?

00:44:58.890 --> 00:45:01.450
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I've already
started interviewing.

00:45:01.450 --> 00:45:03.820
I've clocked about a
dozen interviews so far

00:45:03.820 --> 00:45:07.930 position:56%
and I'm gathering newspaper
articles, trying to focus on the end

00:45:07.930 --> 00:45:13.630
of professional baseball in Cuba,
essentially sort of 1958 to 1961,

00:45:13.630 --> 00:45:17.110
what happened with the Cuban
League and the Sugar Kings at the,

00:45:17.110 --> 00:45:20.610
you know, as the revolution
was building and then

00:45:20.610 --> 00:45:23.970
in the immediate aftermath
of the revolution.

00:45:23.970 --> 00:45:32.190
How the league ended, you know,
the last season was 1960-61

00:45:32.190 --> 00:45:37.780
for the Cuban League and it was
an all-Cuban for the first time,

00:45:37.780 --> 00:45:41.450
certainly in the 20th
century, an all-Cuban League

00:45:41.450 --> 00:45:43.580
because U.S. players
were not allowed

00:45:43.580 --> 00:45:46.600
at that point to come and play.

00:45:46.600 --> 00:45:52.150
And the Sugar Kings had to leave
mid-season in 1960 to Jersey City

00:45:52.150 --> 00:45:55.030
and it was abrupt enough
that when they debuted

00:45:55.030 --> 00:45:57.870
in Jersey City they still had
their Sugar Kings uniforms

00:45:57.870 --> 00:46:01.890
on with a patch stitched on across
the chest that said Jersey City.

00:46:01.890 --> 00:46:06.210
It was in July when they moved,

00:46:06.210 --> 00:46:09.820
when essentially the International
League revoked the franchise

00:46:09.820 --> 00:46:11.120
and they had to relocate.

00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:24.970
&gt;&gt; I feel like it's unfair
to put you on the spot

00:46:24.970 --> 00:46:28.660
but what does happen now with the
thawing of relations between U.S.

00:46:28.660 --> 00:46:30.600
and Cuba, will we see more players?

00:46:30.600 --> 00:46:33.210
Will there be a professional
league again?

00:46:33.210 --> 00:46:39.290
Or right now I guess the only
institutionalized baseball is

00:46:39.290 --> 00:46:41.710
through the national team?

00:46:41.710 --> 00:46:44.040
&gt;&gt; Right. Well, I think
we're going to see some sort

00:46:44.040 --> 00:46:45.460
of system in place eventually.

00:46:45.460 --> 00:46:48.270
How long that will
take I don't know.

00:46:48.270 --> 00:46:52.630
I can tell you that there's
a group here, people who used

00:46:52.630 --> 00:46:57.770 position:56%
to be associated with the
Pawtucket Red Sox who own the rights

00:46:57.770 --> 00:47:03.120
to a future minor league team in
Havana should there ever be one.

00:47:03.120 --> 00:47:07.670
They've been working to build
relationships with the people

00:47:07.670 --> 00:47:11.840
in Cuba, the officials
there, you know,

00:47:11.840 --> 00:47:14.340
but right now they're just kind of.

00:47:14.340 --> 00:47:18.890
They're just building relationships
in case there is an opportunity.

00:47:18.890 --> 00:47:25.540
How exactly that would play out
given the economics of the country,

00:47:25.540 --> 00:47:31.150
given the embargo still being in
place, yet to be seen I suspect

00:47:31.150 --> 00:47:35.550 position:56%
as far as Cuban players playing in
the majors and not having to defect,

00:47:35.550 --> 00:47:37.550
I think we will see something.

00:47:37.550 --> 00:47:41.000 position:56%
Maybe it will be a system similar to
what we see with the Japanese League

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:45.270
where a major league team will
essentially bid for the right

00:47:45.270 --> 00:47:48.030
to negotiate with a player,
whatever pool of players

00:47:48.030 --> 00:47:51.840
that they make available and then

00:47:51.840 --> 00:47:55.290
if they negotiate a
contract I suspect part

00:47:55.290 --> 00:47:57.990
of that money will go back
to the Cuban government

00:47:57.990 --> 00:48:02.000
and they will have some sort
of control over his services.

00:48:02.000 --> 00:48:07.750
Cuba had already started sort of
allowing veteran players to play

00:48:07.750 --> 00:48:12.390
in Japan after, you know sort
of as a reward for playing,

00:48:12.390 --> 00:48:16.460
for a distinguished career and not
defecting [laughter] from Cuba.

00:48:16.460 --> 00:48:22.020
So, but usually they've
been late in their careers

00:48:22.020 --> 00:48:24.770
and have not necessarily
had the kind of impact

00:48:24.770 --> 00:48:27.140
that certainly Major League
Baseball would be looking

00:48:27.140 --> 00:48:31.190
for so yes, I think it will happen.

00:48:31.190 --> 00:48:34.020
I think there might still be a
ways away although the one thing

00:48:34.020 --> 00:48:37.790
that made me think it might happen
quicker was the goodwill tour

00:48:37.790 --> 00:48:41.270
that baseball took in
December I think it was

00:48:41.270 --> 00:48:42.980
where they went to Cuba.

00:48:42.980 --> 00:48:46.100 position:56%
And but what they brought with them,
